    "\n",
    "# NGL extraction and fractionation with NeqSim\n",
    "\n",
    "**Audience.** Process, gas-processing, and production engineers who want a reproducible\n",
    "introduction to turbo-expander NGL recovery and fractionation.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prerequisites.** Basic phase equilibrium, material balances, compressors, separators,\n",
    "and distillation are helpful. The notebook installs the public PyPI package when needed.\n",
    "No local files, secrets, or proprietary assays are required.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Learning objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "After completing the notebook you can:\n",
    "\n",
    "- build a characterized rich-gas fluid with named components and TBP fractions;\n",
    "- explain how SRK, flashes, streams, and unit operations form a NeqSim workflow;\n",
    "- condition, expand, separate, and recompress a realistic gas feed;\n",
    "- configure deethanizer and debutanizer columns with the MESH-residual solver;\n",
    "- retrieve compact stream, composition, recovery, energy, gas-quality, and TVP results;\n",
    "- audit overall and component balances;\n",
    "- evaluate cooling-temperature sensitivity with independently initialized cases; and\n",
    "- reuse a validated end-to-end NGL process function in design studies."
   ]
  },
