    "## Engineering context\n",
    "\n",
    "Natural-gas liquids are recovered by cooling and expanding rich gas until a hydrocarbon\n",
    "liquid forms. A scrubber separates the cold liquid. The residue gas is warmed and compressed\n",
    "for export, while the liquid is fractionated. A deethanizer removes methane and ethane; a\n",
    "debutanizer separates LPG-range components from C5+ condensate.\n",
    "\n",
    "The notebook uses a synthetic teaching assay. It demonstrates process logic and supported\n",
    "NeqSim functionality, but it is not a licensor design, a vendor guarantee, or a substitute\n",
    "for exchanger pinch, column hydraulics, rotating-equipment maps, relief, controls, materials,\n",
    "and operability studies."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "66b4dbfb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Governing equations\n",
    "\n",
    "For a steady process without accumulation, the overall mass balance is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\dot{m}_{feed} = \\dot{m}_{gas} + \\dot{m}_{LPG} + \\dot{m}_{C5+}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "For component $i$, recovery to the two liquid products is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "R_i = \\frac{\\dot{n}_{i,LPG} + \\dot{n}_{i,C5+}}{\\dot{n}_{i,feed}}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Here $\\dot{m}$ is mass flow in kg/h and $\\dot{n}_i$ is component molar flow in mol/s.\n",
    "All recoveries are dimensionless."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9aa95498",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "An adiabatic expander converts a fraction of the ideal isentropic enthalpy drop to shaft\n",
    "work:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\eta_s = \\frac{h_{in} - h_{out}}{h_{in} - h_{out,s}}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The stream energy balance for a heat exchanger is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\dot{Q}_{hot} + \\dot{Q}_{cold} = 0\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Here $h$ is specific enthalpy in J/kg, $\\eta_s$ is isentropic efficiency, and $\\dot{Q}$\n",
    "is heat duty in W. Pressure drops, heat loss, and mechanical losses beyond the specified\n",
    "efficiencies are neglected in this teaching model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f5b3f1d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## NeqSim model and solver workflow\n",
    "\n",
    "NeqSim stores composition, temperature, pressure, phases, and properties in a thermodynamic\n",
    "system. The SRK equation of state is chosen because it is a common first model for\n",
    "hydrocarbon-gas processing. The classic mixing rule is retained from the legacy example.\n",
    "\n",
    "`Stream` objects carry cloned fluid states between equipment. `Cooler`, `Expander`,\n",
    "`Separator`, `ThrottlingValve`, `DistillationColumn`, `Mixer`, `Heater`, and `Compressor`\n",
    "objects transform those states. `ProcessSystem` executes them in dependency order. Both\n",
    "columns use NeqSim's simultaneous MESH-residual solver: material, equilibrium, summation,\n",
    "and heat equations are solved together."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "9bdfb8c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
